## MIXA-006 Complete

**Task**: Implement tab system with Chromium webviews
**Status**: All acceptance criteria met, all backpressure gates passed, committed.

### What was built:

**Main Process** (`src/main/tabs/manager.ts`):
- `TabManager` class managing `WebContentsView` instances for each web tab
- Lifecycle: create, activate, destroy web views
- Navigation: back, forward, reload, navigate to URL
- Event forwarding: title updates, favicon changes, URL changes, loading state → renderer via IPC
- Window resize handling to keep views properly bounded
- Security: sandbox enabled, nodeIntegration disabled, contextIsolation enabled

**Renderer** (new files):
- `stores/tabs.ts` — Zustand store with full tab state management (add, close, activate, move, update)
- `components/TabBar.tsx` — Tab strip with drag-and-drop reorder, favicons, loading spinners, close buttons, active indicator
- `components/Toolbar.tsx` — Navigation buttons (back/forward/reload) + URL display with HTTPS lock icon
- `components/TabContent.tsx` — Placeholder content for non-web tab types + new tab page
- `hooks/useTabEvents.ts` — Subscribes to main process events, syncs to Zustand
- `hooks/useTabShortcuts.ts` — Cmd+T, Cmd+W, Cmd+1-9 keyboard shortcuts
- `hooks/useTabLifecycle.ts` — Creates/destroys BrowserViews when tabs are added/removed

**Preload** (`preload/index.ts`):
- Extended with full `tabs` API: createWebView, destroyWebView, activate, navigate, goBack, goForward, reload
- Event listeners: onLoading, onStateChanged, onTitleUpdated, onFaviconUpdated, onUrlUpdated

**App.tsx**: Rewired as browser chrome layout with TabBar + Toolbar + content area